.SH NAME
SVGGraphicsElement.getBBox \- SVGGraphicsElement: getBBox() method
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]SVGGraphicsElement.getBBox()\f[B]\f[R] method allows us
to determine the coordinates of the smallest rectangle in which the
object fits.
The coordinates returned are with respect to the current SVG space
(after the application of all geometry attributes on all the elements
contained in the target element).
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] \f[CR]getBBox()\f[R] must return the actual bounding box
at the time the method was called\(emeven in case the element has not
yet been rendered.
It also does not account for any transformation applied to the element
or its parents.
.RE
.RS
.PP
\f[B]Note:\f[R] \f[CR]getBBox\f[R] returns different values than
\f[CR]getBoundingClientRect()\f[R], as the latter returns value relative
to the viewport
.RE
.SH SYNTAX
.IP
.EX
getBBox()
getBBox(options)
.EE
.SS Parameters
.TP
\f[B]options\f[R] \f[I](experimental)\f[R] \f[I](optional)\f[R]
An options dictionary used to control which parts of the element are
included in the bounding box.
The available options are:
.RS
.TP
\f[B]fill\f[R]
A boolean value indicating that the fill should be included in the
bounding box, defaults to \f[CR]true\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]stroke\f[R]
A boolean value indicating that the stroke should be included in the
bounding box, defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]markers\f[R]
A boolean value indicating that the markers should be included in the
bounding box, defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.TP
\f[B]clipped\f[R]
A boolean value indicating that the bounding box should be clipped,
defaults to \f[CR]false\f[R].
.RE
.SS Return value
The returned value is an \f[CR]SVGRect\f[R] object, which defines the
bounding box.
This value is irrespective of any transformation attribute applied to it
or the parent elements.
